27:29.515 --> 27:32.038
Today's message is titled, Logs on the Fire.

27:32.659 --> 27:34.321
And it's all about dating.

27:35.042 --> 27:40.790
When I asked my now wife, Sarah, the first time to go on a date, I called her from a Motorola flip phone.

27:41.871 --> 27:43.373
Thing weighed like 10 pounds.

27:44.074 --> 27:46.738
I was on my way to a blockbuster video.

27:47.042 --> 27:51.789
to rent a movie, was driving by her house and use that as an opportunity to call.

27:51.849 --> 27:55.374
Now, in my brain, here's what I thought the conversation sounded like.

27:55.715 --> 28:01.323
She picked up the phone and said, hello, and I said, hey, is your last name Campbell's?

28:01.343 --> 28:02.865
Cause you looking mm-mm good.

28:05.229 --> 28:06.491
That's my best pickup line.

28:06.591 --> 28:07.152
Okay.

28:07.172 --> 28:09.616
I don't even know people eat Campbell's soup anymore, but I hope they do.

28:09.696 --> 28:11.038
Cause that's just a great pickup line.

28:11.699 --> 28:14.002
Now that's what I thought it sounded like.

28:14.338 --> 28:16.681
In reality, here's what it actually sounded like.

28:16.721 --> 28:19.585
She picked up the phone, hello, and I'm like, hi!

28:20.427 --> 28:24.032
This is Jason, you know, voice cracking 17 year old, didn't go great.

28:24.713 --> 28:30.601
I don't remember exactly what we talked about, but I do remember there was a Motorola flip phone and a blockbuster video involved.

28:31.282 --> 28:36.850
Today, there is over 100 million people on dating apps like Hinge and Tinder.

28:37.506 --> 28:47.281
And the way that Tinder works is that you scroll through a list of prospective people that you would be interested in, you swipe left if you're not interested, you swipe right if you are.

28:48.042 --> 28:49.264
It's kind of like Amazon Prime.

28:49.444 --> 28:52.208
You're like, eh, whatever, we'll give it a shot.

28:53.090 --> 28:56.335
Now I'm not saying there's anything wrong with online dating.

28:56.375 --> 28:58.879
In fact, I actually think online dating is a great tool.

28:59.099 --> 29:02.464
I talk to people all the time who are married and they say we met online.

29:03.025 --> 29:06.450
And it's a great way to find out people who share the same values that you do.

29:07.042 --> 29:15.892
But I would argue that this generation seems to be the most confused generation in history when it comes to dating.

29:16.913 --> 29:27.364
And the reason why I think it might be the most confused generation in history when it comes to dating is because it's also the most deceived generation in history when it comes to dating.

29:28.025 --> 29:29.226
Just think about this for a second.

29:29.246 --> 29:32.530
We have told a whole generation of kids, follow your heart,

29:33.602 --> 29:34.764
How are you gonna make good decisions?

29:34.804 --> 29:35.825
How are you gonna know who to date?

29:35.865 --> 29:38.869
All you just follow your heart, you'll make great decisions that way.

29:38.889 --> 29:42.433
We've told the whole generation of kids, you gotta find the one.

29:43.495 --> 29:46.779
Who's that one person that's going to complete you?

29:47.981 --> 29:53.047
We've told the whole generation, you need to live together before marriage to find out if you're gonna be good roommates.

29:53.368 --> 30:01.298
You need to sleep together before marriage to find out if you're gonna be physically compatible, all of which are not true.

30:01.922 --> 30:06.610
was watching a clip online of a guy who stepped up to the microphone to address a podcaster.

30:06.630 --> 30:08.613
It was kind of an open mic sort of deal.

30:08.994 --> 30:14.583
And he got up to this open mic and he said to the podcaster, he said, I have listened to every podcast you've put out over a year and a half.

30:15.785 --> 30:19.732
I did everything that you have told me to do.

30:19.772 --> 30:23.538
And it has ruined my life and ruined my relationships.

30:24.738 --> 30:31.286
And as you can imagine, this podcaster was taken aback and he's like, what did I say that caused you to ruin lives and ruin relationships?

30:31.526 --> 30:37.913
He said, you said that I should sleep with as many girls as possible, date as many girls as I can.

30:39.275 --> 30:42.699
I did that and it ruined every relationship that I had.

30:43.940 --> 30:45.662
And then he added these words.

30:45.722 --> 30:52.690
He said, it was only when I turned to Jesus Christ that my life began to change for the better.

30:53.410 --> 30:55.953
and the whole audience began to clap.

30:57.274 --> 31:03.881
I want to say to each of you today that the way that the world has told you to date for the most part is wrong.

31:04.822 --> 31:07.185
And I'm not saying that as somebody who has an arrogant opinion.

31:07.345 --> 31:08.807
You know, my opinion is so important.

31:09.087 --> 31:15.374
I'm saying that as someone who's read what the Bible says about dating, marriage, and relationship.

31:15.394 --> 31:20.359
And so I want to take you today to what does the Bible say about dating, marriage, and relationships?

31:20.419 --> 31:22.802
And what it has to say is not just for young adults,

31:23.746 --> 31:28.792
If you're single here today and you're in your 40s, 50s, and 60s, I believe this is going to speak into your life.

31:30.414 --> 31:36.781
If you are divorced or widowed, I believe that God can use this to guide you in this season.

31:38.043 --> 31:43.048
And if you're a parent or a grandparent and your kids are coming to you and going, well, who should I date?

31:43.349 --> 31:44.130
How should I date?

31:44.490 --> 31:48.695
I'm hopeful that you'll have more to say to them than just, well, you'll kind of figure it out.

31:49.896 --> 31:51.378
Cause that's part of the problem.

31:52.034 --> 31:58.383
Part of the problem that young people are facing today is that many of them have not seen a healthy dating relationship.

31:59.645 --> 32:03.611
Many of them have not seen a healthy marriage relationship.

32:04.452 --> 32:09.961
So today I wanna take you to Ephesians chapter five and show you what does the Bible say about marriage.

32:10.542 --> 32:11.803
Now you might think that's kind of odd.

32:12.324 --> 32:13.706
Cause you're like, well, hold on a second.

32:13.726 --> 32:17.532
Like why are you talking about marriage in a message on dating?

32:18.553 --> 32:21.618
The reason why I wanna show you what the Bible says about marriage

32:22.146 --> 32:29.693
is because the end goal of dating is to find someone you want to spend the rest of your life with.

32:30.935 --> 32:34.818
The end goal of dating is to find a future spouse.

32:34.878 --> 32:36.180
It's not to find yourself.

32:37.341 --> 32:41.144
You don't need to use someone else to find yourself.

32:41.164 --> 32:45.849
You don't need to toy with someone else's emotions in order to find your self.

32:45.929 --> 32:49.032
The end goal of dating is to find someone to marry.

32:49.913 --> 32:50.994
That doesn't mean

32:51.618 --> 32:54.103
that you should talk about marriage on your second date.

32:54.964 --> 32:56.166
Okay, I would not recommend doing that.

32:57.469 --> 32:58.470
But here's what it does mean.

32:59.312 --> 33:02.878
It means that you date with the end goal in mind.

33:03.780 --> 33:05.483
Too many people today date flippantly.

33:06.966 --> 33:07.928
I'm convinced of this.

33:09.050 --> 33:11.394
Just because someone flirts with you doesn't mean you should go out with them.

33:12.496 --> 33:15.922
Just because someone shows interest in you doesn't mean that you should date them.

33:16.450 --> 33:18.852
But they're interested in me and that makes me feel so good.

33:18.912 --> 33:22.836
And I want to be like, yeah, okay, that's great, but marriage is for life.

33:24.338 --> 33:28.082
This is the second most important decision you will ever make in your life.

33:29.503 --> 33:38.572
After whether or not to put your faith in Jesus Christ, who you marry is the second most important decision that you will ever make.

33:40.354 --> 33:44.498
Don't date flippantly, date with the end goal in mind.

33:45.090 --> 33:47.433
Here's what the Bible says about marriage and Ephesians chapter five.

33:48.935 --> 33:57.506
It says, husbands, love your wives just as Christ loved the church and gave himself up for her.

33:59.609 --> 34:02.032
If you are a woman and you're wondering, well, who should I date?

34:03.474 --> 34:04.215
Look for this guy.

34:06.137 --> 34:12.946
Look for someone who will love you as Jesus Christ loved the church and was willing to lay down his life for it.

34:14.530 --> 34:23.445
That means he's not someone who's selfish, he's not focused on himself and self-centered, he's not pointing people to himself, he's pointing people to Jesus Christ.

34:24.908 --> 34:30.758
Paul goes on in verse 32 and he says this, this, he's been talking about marriage is a profound mystery.

34:31.799 --> 34:33.082
What is the mystery he's referring to?

34:33.843 --> 34:35.846
He says, well, I'm talking about Christ in the church.

34:36.868 --> 34:40.434
In other words, I'm not just talking about marriage, I'm actually talking about Christ in the church.

34:41.026 --> 34:49.917
However, each one of you also must love his wife as he loves himself and the wife must respect her husband.

34:51.499 --> 34:53.341
Why did God create marriage?

34:54.402 --> 35:00.350
Why did God have the idea that a man would leave his father and mother and be united to his wife and the two would become one?

35:00.450 --> 35:01.391
Why did God do that?

35:01.411 --> 35:02.212
What's the point?

35:02.232 --> 35:02.813
What's the purpose?

35:04.094 --> 35:10.322
The point and the purpose is to point people to the love and the intimacy that Jesus Christ has for his church.

35:11.106 --> 35:20.440
that marriage is a tangible way for us to see and to taste the love and the intimacy that God has.

35:20.721 --> 35:24.026
That is the mystery that Paul is referring to.

35:25.168 --> 35:28.332
But notice at the end what he said about wives.

35:28.352 --> 35:31.377
He said, you must respect your husband.

35:32.919 --> 35:37.266
Guys, you are looking for a woman, a wife, who will respect you.

35:38.050 --> 35:41.394
Not just who you find attractive, not just who flirts with you.

35:41.434 --> 35:45.219
You're looking for someone who will respect you.

35:45.259 --> 35:50.645
In fact, if you are a guy or a girl and you're dating someone right now and you're wondering, well, should we get married?

35:51.706 --> 35:53.409
Here's the question you ought to be asking.

35:53.809 --> 35:57.834
Will we reflect the love of Jesus Christ better together or apart?

35:59.396 --> 36:04.562
Will we be able to serve Jesus Christ better if we're together and married or if we're apart?

36:05.506 --> 36:07.969
If you're looking at your relationship and you're going, you know what?

36:08.510 --> 36:11.173
We will reflect the love of Jesus Christ better together.

36:11.934 --> 36:14.577
We will be able to serve Jesus Christ better together.

36:14.797 --> 36:16.379
Then you should get married.

36:17.801 --> 36:20.304
But if you're looking at that question, you're going, I don't know.

36:22.587 --> 36:24.710
I'm not sure we would serve Jesus better together.

36:24.730 --> 36:28.895
I'm not sure I would reflect the love of Jesus better if I was in a relationship with that person.

36:30.176 --> 36:31.538
Then you're better off being single.

36:32.642 --> 36:35.946
Cause look at what the Bible says in 1 Corinthians chapter seven to people who are single.

36:36.486 --> 36:39.289
Paul says this, if you do get married, it's not a sin.

36:42.653 --> 36:43.674
That's good news, right?

36:43.694 --> 36:45.957
For those of us who are married are like, okay, it's not going great, but it wasn't a sin.

36:48.440 --> 36:54.006
He says, however, I'm trying to spare you the extra problems that come with it.

36:56.449 --> 36:58.331
If you're married, don't look at your spouse right now.

37:00.113 --> 37:01.074
But do you know what they are?

37:02.274 --> 37:03.155
They're a problem.

37:04.477 --> 37:05.939
They're a real problem, aren't they?

37:07.100 --> 37:08.502
And I'll tell single people this.

37:08.522 --> 37:09.844
I'll say, you know, they're kind of a problem.

37:09.864 --> 37:13.228
And they'll look at me confused and they'll go, I thought he was gonna complete me.

37:14.250 --> 37:15.051
No, that's a movie.

37:16.773 --> 37:17.854
He's not going to complete you.

37:17.894 --> 37:21.059
He'll completely leave his underwear on the bathroom floor six days in a row.

37:21.079 --> 37:22.721
He's not going to complete you.

37:22.761 --> 37:27.867
Here's what he says in the next verse.

37:27.888 --> 37:29.810
He says an unmarried man.

37:30.754 --> 37:34.579
can spend his time doing the Lord's work and thinking of how to please him.

37:35.681 --> 37:37.403
But a married man can't do that so well.

37:38.445 --> 37:42.871
He has to think about his earthly responsibilities and how to please his wife.

37:44.353 --> 37:51.263
What I wanted you to see from these verses is how differently the Bible speaks about singleness than what we're used to in our culture.

37:52.585 --> 37:57.552
If you listen to people in our culture talk about being single, it's almost like it's this death sentence.

37:58.433 --> 37:59.314
Have you met someone yet?

37:59.778 --> 38:00.900
Are you dating anyone yet?

38:01.641 --> 38:04.164
You know, you go to grandma's house and she's like, are you in a relay?

38:04.184 --> 38:04.905
He met somebody.

38:05.766 --> 38:10.613
You're like, I gotta get through this season as quickly as possible.

38:12.135 --> 38:14.519
If you're single today, I just want you to take a breath.

38:16.682 --> 38:19.666
Jesus was single, Paul was single.

38:20.447 --> 38:23.111
There's many benefits to being single.

38:23.151 --> 38:28.178
You have the time to give God your undivided attention and to serve Him.

38:28.834 --> 38:30.596
Paul even says this a few verses later.

38:31.437 --> 38:36.563
He says, the person who marries does well and the person who doesn't marry does even better.

38:39.366 --> 38:40.046
It's in the Bible.

38:40.287 --> 38:45.673
I was like, I must have missed that verse before I got married.

38:48.075 --> 38:48.796
Now I'm married.

38:48.856 --> 38:49.797
I'm not against marriage.

38:49.817 --> 38:50.658
I'm all for marriage.

38:50.698 --> 38:52.981
I love when I hear people, you know, getting married, starting families.

38:53.001 --> 38:54.162
That's a gift from God.

38:55.042 --> 39:01.252
But what Paul is saying here is he's like, yeah, you did well if you got married, but if you're single in many ways, that can be even better.

39:01.913 --> 39:03.075
Here's what I want you to see today.

39:03.456 --> 39:07.162
Singleness isn't a time to despise, it is a time to embrace.

39:08.724 --> 39:12.791
So I wanna show you two principles that I hope you build into your life before you start dating.

39:13.111 --> 39:17.298
And here's the first one, don't follow your heart, follow godly wisdom.

39:18.594 --> 39:22.438
I had my son had a basketball tournament, all day tournament down in Rosemont years ago.

39:22.478 --> 39:23.700
And I was speaking here at church.

39:23.720 --> 39:25.922
And so I drove down right afterwards and watched two of his games.

39:26.403 --> 39:28.005
And afterwards I was just starving.

39:29.166 --> 39:31.308
And so my kids were like, hey, let's stop and get fast food.

39:31.328 --> 39:32.610
And I'm like, no, we're gonna save money.

39:32.630 --> 39:33.511
We're gonna eat at home.

39:33.971 --> 39:35.513
And then we stopped at a gas station.

39:36.755 --> 39:38.216
And my son said, can we just get a snack?

39:39.277 --> 39:40.379
And I was so hungry.

39:40.479 --> 39:41.800
And so I never go get snacks.

39:41.820 --> 39:44.003
I just don't think of going inside at a gas station.

39:44.023 --> 39:44.784
But I was like, sure.

39:44.804 --> 39:46.866
So I went inside, he went to the bathroom.

39:47.490 --> 39:55.481
When he came back to the register, I was standing up there with two Italian sandwiches, Lunchables, Cheese Pringles, Twix Ice Cream.

39:56.542 --> 39:58.024
My son was in shock.

39:59.226 --> 40:02.530
My digestive system was in shock later on that night.

40:04.613 --> 40:06.515
People do dumb stuff when they're hungry.

40:08.418 --> 40:10.621
People do really dumb stuff when they're hungry for love.

40:11.983 --> 40:17.490
Solomon, one of the wisest people who's ever lived, he said this, promise me, O women of Jerusalem,

40:17.986 --> 40:21.870
not to awaken love until the time is right.

40:24.052 --> 40:24.953
He says, slow down.

40:26.795 --> 40:30.820
Don't date when you're hungry because people make bad decisions when they're hungry.

40:31.821 --> 40:35.845
One of the mistakes that single people can frequently make is they move too quickly.

40:37.006 --> 40:41.151
Two months after a breakup in a serious relationship, already dating someone else.

40:42.152 --> 40:43.073
I'm like, whoa, slow down.

40:43.113 --> 40:44.434
You haven't healed from the last one.

40:45.794 --> 40:48.457
few months after a divorce, already in another relationship.

40:50.179 --> 40:50.599
Slow down.

40:50.799 --> 40:54.303
You haven't learned what you needed to learn from that previous relationship.

40:55.545 --> 40:58.748
Have you seen the person that you're dating when they're stressed?

40:58.768 --> 41:00.150
Have you seen them when they're angry?

41:00.190 --> 41:02.032
Have you seen them when they're not at their best?

41:02.272 --> 41:04.835
You need to see them in those kinds of environments.

41:06.216 --> 41:10.521
Solomon said, don't awaken love until the time is right.

41:11.202 --> 41:13.003
Here's what a lot of us do when we first meet someone.

41:14.265 --> 41:15.346
We put on a pair of these.

41:17.250 --> 41:18.271
rose-colored glasses.

41:19.392 --> 41:23.256
So when you look at his work ethic, here's what you see.

41:24.638 --> 41:32.146
And when your godly parents look at his work ethic, here's what they see.

41:32.166 --> 41:34.608
When you look at his temper, here's what you see.

41:34.648 --> 41:39.153
And when other people look at his temper, here's what they see.

41:41.035 --> 41:43.698
It's rose-colored glasses.

41:44.482 --> 41:50.711
Now studies have shown infatuation happens in every relationship and in fact it's impossible to not go through an infatuation stage.

41:51.072 --> 41:56.119
But they've done studies on this and they've found that infatuation shuts down your brain.

41:57.521 --> 41:58.763
You're not seeing clearly.

41:59.964 --> 42:01.246
You're not thinking clearly.

42:02.568 --> 42:06.153
That's why godly outside advice is so important.

42:07.195 --> 42:09.298
Notice I said the word godly.

42:10.402 --> 42:17.854
If your godly family members, if your godly friends are uncomfortable with your relationship, that ought to be a huge red flag.

42:19.436 --> 42:22.481
Don't just listen to your heart.

42:22.501 --> 42:23.683
Don't just follow your heart.

42:24.103 --> 42:25.505
Follow wisdom.

42:26.267 --> 42:29.011
Here's some wisdom for you in your life.

42:29.392 --> 42:36.002
Dating is a time for discernment, not devotion.

42:36.022 --> 42:38.706
Dating is a time for discernment, not devotion.

42:40.098 --> 42:42.341
Marriage is the opposite of that, by the way.

42:43.323 --> 42:50.452
If you're married and you're looking around going, oh boy, I think I made the wrong decision, wish I would have married that person, you need to do everything you can to get rid of those thoughts.

42:52.135 --> 42:55.159
You need to take those thoughts captive and make them obedient to Jesus Christ.

42:55.399 --> 42:59.665
You need to focus on being committed and fulfilling the promise you made before God.

43:00.987 --> 43:05.874
But dating is a time for discernment, especially early in the relationship.

43:06.978 --> 43:14.306
What oftentimes happens to single people is we move towards devotion too quickly and we short change the discernment process.

43:15.727 --> 43:26.859
If you become emotionally attached too quickly and you move too fast with your heart and with your emotions, it almost becomes impossible to make discerning decisions.

43:28.321 --> 43:32.946
This is one of the reasons why I believe that God says, wait until marriage to have sex.

43:34.626 --> 43:41.855
Because when you have sex with another person, you are becoming one, not just physically, but spiritually and emotionally.

43:42.095 --> 43:50.245
And when you are that connected to another person, it becomes almost impossible to make discerning decisions regarding their character.

43:51.206 --> 43:52.107
Proverbs 4.23.

43:53.809 --> 44:01.298
Solomon says this, he says, above all else, above everything else, guard your heart,

44:02.178 --> 44:04.822
for everything you do flows from it.

44:06.405 --> 44:07.907
Don't follow your heart.

44:08.207 --> 44:10.772
He says, guard your heart.

44:11.933 --> 44:12.735
Are you doing that?

44:14.177 --> 44:15.499
Are you guarding your heart?

44:17.041 --> 44:19.445
Are you guarding the heart of the person that you're dating?

44:20.807 --> 44:23.311
The person you're dating right now, that might not be your wife.

44:23.351 --> 44:25.074
That might not be your future husband.

44:26.210 --> 44:32.237
You don't want them to enter into a relationship with someone else someday with baggage from your relationship.

44:33.879 --> 44:34.801
Guard their heart.

44:36.182 --> 44:37.304
How do you guard a person's heart?

44:37.324 --> 44:38.565
Well, first of all, you're honest.

44:40.127 --> 44:43.651
If you're not feeling the relationship, if you don't see it going anywhere, just tell them that.

44:44.853 --> 44:47.036
Be as kind as you can, but be as honest as you can.

44:47.536 --> 44:48.277
Slow down.

44:48.918 --> 44:52.042
There's a natural progression to emotions in relationships.

44:53.604 --> 44:55.506
Don't pressure them into having sex.

44:57.058 --> 45:02.825
If you're a guy and you're in a relationship right now and you are pressuring your girlfriend to have sex, I'm gonna say this to you directly.

45:03.045 --> 45:04.647
You do not love her like you think you do.

45:07.731 --> 45:10.034
You think that you love her, you're telling her, but I really love each other.

45:10.234 --> 45:11.335
We should take it to the next level.

45:11.596 --> 45:13.919
You are not loving her like Christ loved the church.

45:15.220 --> 45:19.586
You are not laying down what you want and what you desire for the sake of what's better for her.

45:22.609 --> 45:26.514
Don't follow your heart, follow godly wisdom.

45:27.202 --> 45:30.668
I had a chance to sit down with some singles in our church this week to hear their wisdom.

45:31.430 --> 45:34.435
And in this video, you're gonna see there's one of the couples that's dating each other.

45:34.736 --> 45:37.220
The other ones are sitting by each other, but they're not actually dating each other.

45:37.240 --> 45:37.962
They're single.

45:38.723 --> 45:43.472
And you're gonna get to hear some wisdom from people in our church who are single and dating.

45:43.892 --> 45:44.854
And what is that like?

45:44.914 --> 45:46.537
I thought it was a really interesting conversation.

45:46.577 --> 45:47.058
Take a look.

46:03.682 --> 46:04.964
Well, thank you guys for being here.

46:05.184 --> 46:06.866
I'm really excited about this conversation.

46:07.187 --> 46:09.890
We're in a series of, you know, cabin fever, and it's all about relationships.

46:10.431 --> 46:11.673
And this week has been about dating.

46:11.853 --> 46:15.338
And I just thought it'd be really interesting to hear from people in our church who are single dating.

46:15.358 --> 46:16.479
You guys are dating one another.

46:16.820 --> 46:20.425
But just to hear, what is it like these days to be single, to be dating?

46:20.505 --> 46:21.967
And what would you say to our church?

46:21.987 --> 46:23.168
So we're going to start with this question.

46:23.589 --> 46:25.051
What is the hardest part of dating?

46:25.952 --> 46:27.614
I feel like we're all distracted.

46:27.855 --> 46:28.195
I don't know.

46:28.355 --> 46:30.418
Our attention is constantly being pulled.

46:30.626 --> 46:38.758
so many different directions with politics and social media and it's hard to feel like you're having that human interaction.

46:39.639 --> 46:43.184
It feels difficult to keep it real.

46:43.925 --> 46:45.868
Today it feels like there's a lack of curiosity.

46:46.389 --> 46:50.415
Like that word keeps coming back to me is people don't know how to be curious and ask good questions.

46:51.116 --> 46:58.226
We can get all the information from people's social media or you can text and ask all these questions before you even go on a date and so it's like there's a lack of

46:58.402 --> 47:01.845
curiosity, you get in front of a person, I'm like, you don't know what to ask.

47:02.386 --> 47:07.991
When you're having, you know, conversations with people, I think that's better to have in person.

47:08.552 --> 47:14.838
You know, when you've got your phone, you have all this time to kind of curate the perfect person that you want to be or present yourself to be.

47:15.519 --> 47:18.882
And it's just not always reality.

47:18.902 --> 47:21.264
How has your approach to dating changed over time?

47:21.444 --> 47:23.126
You've probably had some experiences in dating.

47:23.586 --> 47:27.410
Talk a little bit about some of the things that you've learned over the years, the wisdom you've gained.

47:27.746 --> 47:36.814
I am learning that I'm a whole person because of Jesus, and no other person is gonna complete me the way that He does.

47:37.695 --> 47:40.098
Like, I am me, and I feel really good about that.

47:40.358 --> 47:43.080
I'm known by Him, and that is what matters most.

47:44.462 --> 47:51.829
He's my first boyfriend, so I never was, like, officially dating anybody in high school, but it felt like very superficial.

47:52.189 --> 47:57.714
So, like, now that we've been dating for so long, I actually get to experience life

47:57.954 --> 48:03.135
with him and like, it just feels so much more real than in high school.

48:03.798 --> 48:07.794
It was like, we're dating because you just think everyone's supposed to date.

48:08.194 --> 48:11.958
You don't really want to date someone's potential like someone that you hope that they will become someday.

48:11.998 --> 48:18.806
And then a lot of people, especially in Christian circles are looking for perfect, like the perfect, the one, the person, like perfection.

48:18.826 --> 48:20.688
And so like, what's the in between there?

48:20.708 --> 48:26.475
It's like the people who have really good patterns and they're seeking God and they're serving in the church.

48:26.895 --> 48:30.459
So I've learned a lot about that in this season.

48:30.920 --> 48:34.304
One of the interesting things I know about you guys is a lot of you serve in our church.

48:34.664 --> 48:36.466
You have used your single years

48:36.834 --> 48:39.678
to serve and to be a part of what God's doing through the church.

48:40.359 --> 48:43.163
How has that impacted your singleness and your dating, do you think?

48:43.583 --> 48:47.989
When our eyes are not on ourselves and we can look to other people and we stop thinking about what's lacking.

48:48.009 --> 48:52.736
I think for me, being able to serve and be able to see that and be like, hey God, I see what you're doing and I wanna be a part of it.

48:53.317 --> 48:57.623
And not that dating and marriage and having kids is a distraction, but it is a time consumer.

48:58.063 --> 49:02.209
Yeah, I mean, Paul talks about that in Corinthians and he's like, if you're married, your attention's divided.

49:02.249 --> 49:05.714
When you're single, you can be fully devoted to serving

49:05.794 --> 49:07.957
How do you deal with loneliness in a healthy way?

49:08.077 --> 49:10.359
Do you go through seasons where you feel a little lonely?

49:10.439 --> 49:13.042
Like, how do you deal with that in a healthy and kind of God-honoring way?

49:13.984 --> 49:19.270
I've got so many friends that are married and one of the first questions I always ask them is, like, hey, like, how do you deal with loneliness in your marriage?

49:19.630 --> 49:23.575
Almost every single one of them has told me, like, marriage does not solve loneliness.

49:24.256 --> 49:27.880
And the only thing that does is that relationship with God.

49:27.960 --> 49:31.704
Like, you can't find that solution to loneliness in another person.

49:32.025 --> 49:33.266
It can only be found in Jesus.

49:33.410 --> 49:45.267
And for me, when I do have those days of loneliness, I'm like, oh, but this isn't something that's gonna be solved by getting into relationship, by getting into marriage, but it's gonna be solved by me getting into my Bible and getting into a relationship with our Lord and Savior.

49:45.748 --> 49:49.253
Loneliness itself isn't inherently bad.

49:49.914 --> 50:01.170
I feel like a lot of growth can come from just being alone and just being able to really figure out what is going on in your life and what are the things you need to work on and what are the things that kind of God is calling you.

50:01.250 --> 50:03.674
to work towards.

50:04.735 --> 50:08.020
We don't live together, so we do have a lot of time where we're alone.

50:08.060 --> 50:16.373
And I would just say I try my best to use that as a time to get my Bible, maybe connect with some of my guy friends.

50:16.473 --> 50:18.276
And then we can use that.

50:18.296 --> 50:21.501
Then when we come together, our faith is stronger.

50:21.521 --> 50:22.623
I just want to follow up real quick.

50:22.643 --> 50:23.564
You said you don't live together.

50:23.604 --> 50:25.948
So many people in our culture do before marriage.

50:26.369 --> 50:27.250
Talk a little bit more about that.

50:27.650 --> 50:42.089
It's a great boundary to have in a Christian dating relationship to not live together because then it just, that temptation is dwindled by so much, which has really been helpful for us.

50:42.930 --> 50:43.951
How do you guys stay patient?

50:44.592 --> 50:46.254
Maybe God's timeline is different than yours.

50:46.314 --> 50:48.377
Maybe you want something and it's not happening.

50:48.397 --> 50:51.080
How have you dealt with that where you've had to kind of wait on God?

50:51.801 --> 50:55.346
Remembering that God has a plan for me

50:55.746 --> 51:01.874
whether that's marriage, whether it's not, that's his plan, and that's the best for me.

51:02.454 --> 51:04.177
What would you say to other singles in our church?

51:04.217 --> 51:07.220
If you had a chance to speak to singles, what would you want to say to them?

51:08.021 --> 51:09.523
Enjoy the space, definitely.

51:09.543 --> 51:20.177
Allow yourself to really hone in on your God-given abilities and the things that God has gifted you in your life.

51:20.777 --> 51:22.720
Your life doesn't start when you start dating somebody.

51:22.740 --> 51:24.562
It doesn't start when you get married.

51:24.770 --> 51:26.733
live your life now, you have so much freedom.

51:26.773 --> 51:27.934
So much freedom.

51:27.954 --> 51:28.896
So much freedom.

51:29.116 --> 51:35.565
And you just get to, you can hang out with your friends and you get to serve a church and you're in this season for a reason.

51:35.765 --> 51:38.369
You're gonna miss it if you're looking so far down the road.

51:39.370 --> 51:40.652
God has not forgotten you.

51:41.133 --> 51:49.344
I think it can be really easy to feel that way, but he sees you, he knows you, he loves you, and he has a plan for you, whatever that is.

51:49.684 --> 51:53.810
And so I think just to be reminded that he sees you.

51:53.954 --> 52:08.718
Worst case scenarios say like you don't find someone, you don't get married, like you get to do your life with Jesus and like you get to spend your life serving Him and you're going to get to heaven someday and you're going to look at God and get to talk about all those things that you got to do here on earth and see all the things that God was doing that you got to be a part of.

52:10.121 --> 52:18.354
In these times I always cling to my favorite verse which is Ephesians 3 20 and I'm just always reminded that God can do a measurely more.

52:18.466 --> 52:19.829
than we can ask or imagine.

52:19.869 --> 52:22.174
And his plan is greater than we even know.

52:22.214 --> 52:25.662
And so he can just blow our expectations out of the water.

52:25.702 --> 52:32.357
And it doesn't even have to do with our dating life, but in your personal life, in your family, in all areas of your life.

52:32.437 --> 52:34.662
And I've seen him show up in those areas.

52:34.802 --> 52:38.450
And I can trust that and know that because he's shown up time and time again.

52:38.818 --> 52:40.741
Thank you guys for your time and wisdom.

52:40.961 --> 52:42.083
I'm just so proud of each of you.

52:42.103 --> 52:54.220
Like when I hear your stories and how you're faithfully serving God and even just knowing you and how many of you guys are using your gifts and how God is using your life right now in the powerful ways that He uses you on Wednesday nights at students and on the weekends.

52:54.480 --> 52:59.307
And my prayer for our church and our singles in our church is that they would begin to use their time that way as well.

52:59.327 --> 53:04.595
And they would find that they can trust God in this season and that He's gonna use other gifts in this season.

53:04.635 --> 53:07.058
So thanks for your time.

53:10.242 --> 53:14.747
There's some amazing young people in our church who are following wisdom.

53:16.148 --> 53:19.752
Second principle that I hope you'll build into your life is this, become the person you wanna date.

53:20.994 --> 53:23.797
Become the person that you want to date.

53:23.837 --> 53:26.099
If you want to date someone who's godly, become godly.

53:26.920 --> 53:29.563
If you wanna date someone who's generous, become generous yourself.

53:29.943 --> 53:31.925
You will never attract what you are not.

53:33.607 --> 53:36.370
If you're like, but I want this person to be, is that you?

53:36.738 --> 53:40.284
you won't attract a person that you are not.

53:40.604 --> 53:44.551
In fact, a person's past is the best predictor of their future.

53:46.274 --> 53:49.640
An honest single person will often become an honest married person.

53:51.923 --> 53:58.274
A single person who is generous will often become a married person who is generous, but the opposite is also true.

53:59.276 --> 54:03.122
An unhappy single person usually becomes an unhappy married person.

54:03.746 --> 54:07.230
A hot-tempered single person becomes a hot-tempered married person.

54:08.271 --> 54:11.455
We tend to think that marriage is going to eliminate habits.

54:11.475 --> 54:12.936
It actually accentuates them.

54:14.198 --> 54:18.062
Oftentimes the best predictor of a person's future is their past behavior.

54:18.082 --> 54:22.547
It's why I say to single people, pay attention to patterns and not just potential.

54:23.388 --> 54:24.990
You heard Kelsey talk about that on the video.

54:26.051 --> 54:26.751
It's so true.

54:27.592 --> 54:29.695
Don't date for potential, date for patterns.

54:30.496 --> 54:32.658
Potential is, well, he said he'd go to church with me.

54:33.378 --> 54:34.059
That's potential.

54:35.060 --> 54:37.282
Pattern is, he goes now, he's committed to God.

54:38.904 --> 54:44.511
Too many people are dating for potential and they are ignoring patterns in their life.

54:45.091 --> 54:47.134
Now does that mean that a person can't change?

54:47.194 --> 54:47.955
Well no, of course not.

54:48.816 --> 54:49.857
People change all the time.

54:50.818 --> 54:53.841
But God is the one who changes them, not us.

54:54.542 --> 54:56.144
I wanna show you this verse from Proverbs.

54:57.646 --> 55:01.490
It says, charm is deceptive and beauty is fleeting.

55:02.242 --> 55:04.765
but a woman who fears the Lord is to be praised.

55:05.766 --> 55:12.113
Now this verse was written to women, but I think it a principle applies to men as well, and the point is beauty is fleeting.

55:12.634 --> 55:13.495
It doesn't last.

55:14.236 --> 55:16.858
In fact, beauty in and of itself is subjective.

55:17.960 --> 55:22.865
In the 16th century, pale skin and double chins were considered attractive.

55:24.047 --> 55:28.011
They would look at us tanning and dieting and going, why are you making yourself look worse?

55:29.413 --> 55:30.674
The ancient Greeks

55:31.010 --> 55:34.495
found unibrow's to be particularly attractive.

55:35.516 --> 55:37.619
NBA player Anthony Davis is like, hey, hey.

55:40.883 --> 55:42.606
We're all the single Greek ladies at, right?

55:44.929 --> 55:46.951
But my point is that beauty is subjective.

55:46.971 --> 55:48.193
It doesn't last.

55:48.273 --> 55:48.934
It's fleeting.

55:49.795 --> 55:52.619
Does that mean that you shouldn't be attracted to the person that you're dating?

55:52.639 --> 55:53.240
No, of course not.

55:53.280 --> 55:54.381
You should be attracted.

55:55.623 --> 55:57.906
But I hope your attraction is more than just skin deep.

55:59.042 --> 56:00.704
What are some of the characteristics to look for?

56:00.964 --> 56:02.145
Look for someone who's humble.

56:03.327 --> 56:04.448
Look for someone who's honest.

56:05.529 --> 56:07.051
Look for someone who is disciplined.

56:07.331 --> 56:09.374
Look for someone who's self-controlled.

56:10.855 --> 56:15.500
Alcohol, anger, drugs, sex, marriage killers.

56:17.342 --> 56:20.506
Talked to couples all the time whose marriage didn't end the way that they hoped it would.

56:20.746 --> 56:23.509
You start asking some questions and talking to them and praying for them.

56:23.710 --> 56:27.634
And here's what you find often, alcohol, anger, drugs, sex.

56:29.346 --> 56:30.547
One of those was involved.

56:32.330 --> 56:34.712
How self-controlled is this person that you're dating?

56:36.435 --> 56:37.776
Are they emotionally steady?

56:37.996 --> 56:41.701
Are they emotionally steady or are they just kind of way up and down?

56:41.761 --> 56:44.424
Are they spiritually steady or are they spiritually up and down?

56:45.546 --> 56:46.807
People will ask me this question.

56:46.947 --> 56:48.990
Should a believer date a non-believer?

56:49.290 --> 56:50.051
And the answer is no.

56:51.192 --> 56:51.973
Here's why I say that.

56:51.993 --> 56:52.734
The Bible says this.

56:52.995 --> 56:55.858
Do not be yoked together with an unbeliever.

56:56.962 --> 57:02.128
A yoke was a piece of farm equipment used to bring two animals together for the purpose of plowing a field.

57:03.210 --> 57:08.776
You would never yoke together a donkey and an ox, because they're gonna pull you in different directions.

57:10.258 --> 57:12.280
It's the same with a believer and an unbeliever.

57:13.302 --> 57:18.388
You get married and all of a sudden you're like, oh, one of them goes, let's get up and go to church.

57:18.408 --> 57:19.830
The other one's like, no, let's sleep in.

57:21.391 --> 57:25.016
One of them says, you know, we should send our kids on that winter retreat for youth group.

57:25.036 --> 57:26.898
And the other one goes, well, they got a tournament that weekend.

57:28.034 --> 57:28.775
They got practice.

57:30.557 --> 57:32.139
One of them says, let's read the Bible, let's pray.

57:32.159 --> 57:33.100
The other one's like, no, it's not.

57:33.400 --> 57:37.144
One of them says, we should tithe 10% to give back to God's work in this world.

57:37.164 --> 57:38.986
And the other one goes, you've got to be kidding me.

57:40.568 --> 57:44.593
A believer and an unbeliever are gonna constantly pull themselves in different directions.

57:46.014 --> 57:48.997
What I always say to single people is this, run to Jesus.

57:50.559 --> 57:51.420
Run towards Jesus.

57:51.701 --> 57:56.626
Spend your single years running towards Him, serving Him, loving Him, obeying Him.

57:57.474 --> 58:14.332
And if at some point, as you are running towards Jesus Christ, you look to your left, or you look to your right, and you see someone who's running right alongside you, not who's way back here somewhere, but someone right alongside you, that is the person that you turn to.

58:15.533 --> 58:19.898
And you say, is your last name Campbell's?

58:19.918 --> 58:21.099
Because you are looking mm-mm good.

58:22.661 --> 58:23.762
Let's pray together as we close.

58:28.418 --> 58:33.004
Lord, I pray for that single person in our church right now who feels as if you've forgotten them.

58:34.767 --> 58:38.452
Remind them, God, of what a season this is in their life to embrace.

58:40.294 --> 58:46.803
And what a powerful season this is, God, for them to use the talents and the gifts and the skills that you've given them to serve you.

58:48.606 --> 58:57.298
God, I pray that they would find such joy and such enjoyment in being used by you to serve and to do work that's gonna reach other people for Christ.

58:58.754 --> 59:02.899
God, I pray for those who are in a dating relationship right now that you would give them wisdom and discernment.

59:04.181 --> 59:05.082
I pray for purity.

59:07.384 --> 59:08.406
God, I pray for honesty.

59:08.426 --> 59:17.416
And God, I pray that they would sharpen one another to run towards Jesus to become more fully devoted to you.

59:20.020 --> 59:25.426
God, I pray for anyone here who's divorced or widowed, single and doesn't want to be.

59:27.394 --> 59:29.678
God made they experience your love and presence in their life.

59:32.303 --> 59:39.997
Maybe they just sense your comfort and your peace, help them to just be settled God and to trust you in the plans that you have for their life right now.

59:42.301 --> 59:47.090
And God, if we're married and have kids, Lord marriage can be really hard.

59:48.482 --> 59:57.432
I pray that we would still date our spouse, that we would still find times of fun with our spouse and that we would love one another as Christ loves the church, that we would be willing to lay down our life.

59:59.315 --> 01:00:02.919
And God, I pray for a husband here if there's something that he needs to lay down for the sake of his wife.

01:00:05.662 --> 01:00:11.149
And I pray for a wife here who needs to encourage and respect her husband in a new, fresh way.

01:00:13.672 --> 01:00:14.633
God, would you give us wisdom?

01:00:14.653 --> 01:00:15.794
Would you give us guidance?

01:00:16.674 --> 01:00:17.977
And we thank you for marriage, God.

01:00:17.997 --> 01:00:25.393
We thank you for the visible symbol that allows us to taste and to see the love that you have for your church and for your people.

01:00:26.655 --> 01:00:28.680
For all these things in Jesus' name, amen.

01:00:29.942 --> 01:00:31.406
Next weekend, we're gonna talk about sex.

01:00:31.726 --> 01:00:32.348
It's gonna be great.

01:00:32.708 --> 01:00:33.490
We'll see you then.

